People complain about getting hit for 600 - 1000 damage. Thats not LA, thats LA + 100% crits. <br>
<br>
Simply leave LA the crap alone! Change berserker frenzy to give a 50% crit 100% of the time, and take away all defensive penalties. Wham bam thank you man, finished, no more 1000+ damage shots and zerkers and SB aren't broken in half. <br>
<br>
<br>
Blademasters: <br>
1) Double-parry check. They should be deadly and defensive. This would make them way more defensive than berserkers. <br>
2) Remove Celtic Duel from them. <br>
3) Make their offhand weapon ALWAYS HIT. Not always swing, ALWAYS CONNECT. Always. <br>
4) Give their mainhand weapon 50% chance to critical hit at all times. <br>
5) Leave Triple-Weild alone.(as in, no frenzy immunity, mmmkay) <br>
6) Remove flurry. <br>
<br>
<br>
Mercenarys: <br>
1) Evade 3. Part of their &quot;unfair play&quot; would be to wear chain armor and still evade like monkeys. <br>
2) Remove Duel Wield from them. <br>
3) Make their offhand weapon ALWAYS HIT. Always. <br>
4) Change Dirty Tricks to a 39% attack speed debuff + 70 point dex/qui debuff in one. Dirty Tricks would no longer be a proc, but a shout on a 20 second recast timer. <br>
5) Give their mainhand weapon a 50% chance to proc an oldschool-dirty-tricks.(35% chance to fumble on target) <br>
6) Remove flurry. <br>
<br>
<br>
This, in my mind, would fix the three light tanks. <br>
Zerkers would still be the monstrous heavy-hitters of the game, but not to the point where they would 1-shot or 2-shot people. <br>
<br>
BMs would be mini-zerkers with higher defense. A great mixture to make the perfect &quot;Blade-MASTER&quot;. No need to spec in CDW allows double-spec or higher defense. <br>
<br>
Mercs would be unfair fighters. Doing everything they can to put the odds in their favor with powerful defensive and offensive debuffs as well as having higher evade with chain armor. No need to spec in DW allows double-spec or higher defense. <br>
<br>
Whats better, is this would officially make all three light tanks the most offensive fighters in their realms.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siryakk>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#000000>(5/8/03 1:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My idea How to fix all three Light Tanks</span><hr size=1> Your suggestion is slightly overpowering.<br>
