<br>
The light tank does 25% more DPS, while the heavy tank takes 20% less melee damage as a fraction of his hitpoints.<br>
<br>
If you work it out, 1.25 * .8 = 1.0, so a light/heavy tank duel would tie.<br>
<br>
Now, take 5 light tanks and 5 heavy tanks (from Albion) and put them up against 10 light tanks (from Hibernia).  Who wins?<br>
<br>
The Hibbies win.  They attack the Albion light tanks first, and drop one before the first Hibernian tank drops.<br>
<br>
By the time all 5 Albion light tanks are dead, there are 6 or 7 Hibernian light tanks standing.  Basically because the Heavy tanks can't tank for their Light tank allies.<br>
<br>
Then, take 10 light tanks vs 5 heavy tanks.  The 10 light lose 1 or 2 tanks.  Same thing happens with 10 heavy vs 5 heavy, except the light tanks win the battle in less time.<br>
<br>
If you want to make light tanks viable, do the following:<br>
<br>
1&gt; Reduce light tank defence, and up their offence a tad.<br>
2&gt; Reduce heavy tank offence, and up their defence a tad.<br>
3&gt; Allow heavy tanks to practially shield and defend light tanks.  Heck, allow light tanks to do the same, to a lesser extent.<br>
<br>
The key part is #3.  Until tanks can actually TANK for another player in RvR all that synergy crap means nothing.  While protect, guard and intercept are cute in PvE, using them in RvR is about as practical as flank styles used to be.  <br>
<br>
Make guard an AoE ability.  Make Intercept an AoE ability.<br>
<br>
Code Protect so that it affects player targetting (if you target a player who is currently being protected by another, and you have LoS to the protector, you will target the protector instead).<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#000000>(5/9/03 12:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My idea How to fix all three Light Tanks</span><hr size=1> I read one persons excuse as to why a light tank should not be able to pull off the same power as a heavy, it was this-<br>
<br>
If a fight between a light tank and a heavy tank comes down to the wire, then the heavy tank is inherently inferior, die to the fact that in RvR the tanks aren't going to be &quot;tanking&quot; so much as &quot;offensing&quot; the enemy casters, healers, bards etc. And if the light tank is able to carry out their duty more efficiently than a heavy tank, then why should anyone play a heavy tank?<br>
<br>
It's a good question and not one that I could answer without being torn to shreds by the wolves.<br>
<br>
But the fact remains that CDW is itself inherently inferior, partly due to our reliance on offense rather than defense to win a fight which, even in PvE is a tough thing to do.<br>
<br>
Check out those Paladins with 42 Shield and no MOB soloing Cthonian Crawlers in Darkness Falls , you'll get what I mean.<br>
<br>
Paladins are built to never die. Mercenaries are supposed to be the true amsters of DoT. It's an idea i totally hate. We're suposed to be shock troops, like less stealthy infils who can cahrge and chop damn fast. <br>
<br>
If I want to deal damage over a long period of time, I'll be a Paladin who can style forever and block forever, and who's HP regenrates as he fights, can stun enemies at will and etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
I won't wait for my End to run out and then cheer, saying&quot; Yee Har! Imagine if I was a polearmsman right now doing only 140% base damage! Well mine is 165%!&quot;<br>
<br>
Because when we run out of endurance that means our enemy is going to shred our lightly armoured bodies. This is DUE to our lack of defense.<br>
<br>
An example I hate to use is the zerker, who charges, takes HELLUVA daamage from everyone hitting him, but deals some HEFTY damage while he can before his end runs out VERY fast . Sort of a crazy fighter, a master of sudden movement, a chaotician or whatever.<br>
<br>
But I don't like that example because I think melee combat (and endurance) should last longer than 20 seconds, even for a light tank, and berzerkers deal mroe damage than anyone should.<br>
<br>
Mythic themself suggested that a mercenary spec 50DW, 44Wep and 39Parry (approximately). But not a lot of mercs I knwo specced that way because they wanted the best offense they could get for the short period they were being torn to shreds.<br>
<br>
And remember that if the only thing we've got over a plate-wearing polearmsman is 22.5% BASE damage (and our styles are only giving us mainhand bonuses for 1H weaponry unlike all other styles which amplify the total damage done *  even the old overpowered Left Axe which was double waht it should be, but in a crappy way, sort of &quot;right&quot;) then we're underpowered when it comes to survival.<br>
<br>
Remembering that a 2H person gets a 40% increase in base damage (making it well worth his while to use a 2H weapon when he doesn't need the defense) just because they DONT HAVE A SHIELD EQUIPPED.<br>
<br>
We can spec less in DW if we like higher parry, because the styles are awful, but we might need a RA to get that dw% aback up, and unless we have maxed DW%, our base damage, the ONLY gap between us and a heavier, more life-prone fighter, is being reduced.<br>
<br>
We're the only class that has to spec heavily in TWO lines in order to keep our base damage over that of a Pally.<br>
<br>
Our offhand is so weak and insignificant (considering its the only thing seperating us from the  other fighters) nobody cares about it any more.<br>
<br>
